 numbers need to be controlled.But of course,should always be despatched cleanly. As was seen at Sandringham.(Died of Gunshot wounds) I wonder if this chap has he ever seen how much damage they can do in a chicken pen ? In the UK,I lost several chickens and knew a farmer who lost 174 chickens in one night to one fox,which I happily shot the next day. I am pleased to say that now living in Australia,we have a more balanced view of animal rights and feral animal control.Of the 67 foxes I have shot here in 4 visits to a farm,none required a second shot and I have saved an awful lot of native animals,reptiles and birds a premature death. As probably more than 95% of the worlds population still eat meat,maybe those less informed might like to educate themselves a little more on where meat actually comes from for a more balanced view.Or they may like to try vegetarianism themselves. I bet not many take up that offer ? john hodson of AUSTRALIA 12:59pm May 30, 2007 Read all 15 comments We welcome your comments on this story. Comments are submitted for possible publication on the condition that they may be edited. Please provide your full name. We also require a working email address - not for publication, but for verification. The location field is optional. Read our publication guidelines Submit your feedback here: (so you don't have to retype your details each time you send feedback) Email me if my comment is published Search for more stories on this topic on , our news archive service. Quit - and stay quit Today marks World No Tobacco Day. Let Quitline help you make the break. More info on quitting Get moving with an E-Toll tag Order your RTA E toll tag at myrta.com 1st mth best package + install 4 NOTHING* Dell + Windows Vista Custom-build a Dell with Windows Vista for a system that works for you TOSHIBA'S LATEST TECRA A8 Lower Temperature. Higher Reliability. It won't just be another day at the office. See the full demo. Receive our News Feeds Get your Newspaper Delive