ence. British special services "asked me to collect compromising information on President (Vladimir) Putin," Lugovoi said. Lugovoi said the attempted recruitment occurred during business trips to Britain in previous years. He did not give a precise date, but indicated the alleged approach occurred in late 2005 or early 2006. London's Foreign Office, responsible for the country's overseas secret intelligence service MI6, declined to comment on Lugovoi's claim. But another government official with knowledge of Lugovoi, who also demanded anonymity because of the sensitivity of the case, said the allegations were untrue. . All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Breaking News: Construction Worker Falls From Lodge Overpass Mazda Recalling 280,000 Cars Northwest Airlines Exits Bankruptcy Ford's Wixom Plant Closes Doors Man Dies In Motorcycle Accident Top Employers For Working Mothers You can have the best of both worlds. Check out which companies do the most to help working mothers. Keep Your Car From Being Stolen Even a car that looks rough can be a target for thieves. Find out how to keep your car from being damaged or stolen. Thinking Of Getting A Time Share? Find out if it's a sound investment or a quick way to throw your money away. What You Need To Know Before You Tie The Knot Find out what you really need to know before you get married. Like video? Click over and check out our new video page we call Links We Like includes a selection of information, tools and resources from our partners and sponsors. Name Released Of TB Patient Military Spouses Become Scam Targets Saab, Volvo Have Safest Convertibles Dad Claims Lohan Hooked On OxyContin Luxury Hotels Cater To Fido More National And World News Experience the one of a kind scene at Movement 07 - Detroit's Electronic Music Festival. Only from the Power of 4, the big event station! Breaking News: Construction Worker Falls From Lodge Overpass Man Dies In Motorcycle