de to $10 billion by 2010 from the current $2. 41 billion a year and promoting Brazilian investment in India’s infrastructure are the thrust areas of Lula’s economic diplomacy in India. Your comment[s] on this article Be the first to comment on this story. New debt instrument with 30-year maturity for banks DoF seeks Rs 18,000 cr to fuel capacity Indian sugar industry may take the Chinese route ...Plans to push raw sugar exports to ease pressure New direct tax code to simplify tax procedures Pay Rs 2 for job guarantee ONGC in swap deal with Brazil’s Petrobras for exploration blocks ...may light up Tripura project with viability gap funding Delhi Metro helped save 33,000 tonne of fuel: report Post-facelist, New Delhi station may put airports to shame BoA to take up 40 SEZ proposals today H-fuel research needs sops: Montek Gujjar stir may hike commodity prices Govt raises TDS threshold for senior citizen savings to Rs 10k New Delhi delays WTO probe on wine duty CWC plans subsidiary for logistics activities Middle-class all set to drive realty market Centre plans package to soften impact of rising rupee on exports McLeod plans branded tea Escorts announces Rs 30-crore upgrade plan JJ Irani Committee On Company Law Run-Up To Foreign Trade Policy 2005-06 Run Up To Budget 2007-08 Rbi Annual Policy 2007-08 Run-Up To Budget 2005-06 Ear To The Ground The Indian Express Group &copy; 2007: Indian Express Newspapers (Mumbai) Ltd. All rights reserved throughout the world.
