 at the Heiligendamm resort on Germany's Baltic Sea coast will bring together the leaders of Britain, Canada, France, Italy, Japan, Russia and the United States. More articles in World &#187; Violent crime on the rise in the US: FBI Senators warn Bush on G8 climate push Rice blasts Chavez closing of Venezuelan TV station (This name will appear below your comment.) (Will not be published.) (Please note: Comment moderation is enabled and may delay your comment. There is no need to resubmit your comment.) Get daily news in your inbox and read it at your convenience. Putin warns retribution for US missile system The big coach hunt Whatmore out, Ford is prime contender for India job Rajasthan burns... Delhi, NCR feel the heat Reliance Fresh set for a roll-out in Mumbai Shilpa Shetty to be honoured at IIFA for global impact BJP hopes hinge on an IITian engineer in Goa Cricket board to name new coach today My film not adapted: Siddharth Anand CMDA erred in sending notice to AIADMK: MK Al Gore against any attempt to impeach Bush Chennai's land prices costlier than London Woman commits suicide as husband refuses to have sex Google to make Web work offline Bollywood in the Big Apple Microsoft rethinks computer with coffee-table design The Universe is Riyo's! Mel Gibson buys $25.8m ranch in Costa Rica US anti-war activist Cindy Sheehan abandons campaign Regular use of laptop could be hazardous Dharavi man held for sexually abusing 11 kids Priyanka signs a three-film deal with UTV ‘My sons are typical Deols’ Russia successfully test fires next generation missile Putin warns retribution for US missile system Six-month traineeship for new coach Russia ups the stakes in US missile shield row A prosecution-defence nexus in BMW case? US anti-war activist Cindy Sheehan abandons campaign Microsoft rethinks computer with coffee-table design Al Gore against any attempt to impeach Bush Puja did not deserve to be Miss Universe: Rohit Bal Bollywood in the Big Apple Indian American husband 